(2x-4y+6)dx + (x+y-3)dy = 0
 x=3-y \wedge 2(3-y)-4y+6=0 \\  x=1 \wedge y=2 \\ k=x-1; \ t=y-2 \\ x=k+1; \ y=t+2 \\ dk=dx;  \ dt=dy \\ (2k-4t)dk=(k+t)dt \\ z(k)=\frac{t}{k} \\ ... 
\frac{dx}{dy} = -\frac{x+y-3}{2x-4y+6}
\frac{dx'}{dy'} = -\frac{x'+y'}{2x'-4y'} = -\frac{1+\frac{y'}{x'}}{2-4\frac{y'}{x'}}
\frac{y'}{x'} = v
y' = vx'
\frac{dy'}{dx'} = v+x'\frac{dv}{dx'}
\frac{dx'}{dy'} = -\frac{x'+y'}{2x'-4y'} = -\frac{1+\frac{y'}{x'}}{2-4\frac{y'}{x'}}
v+x'\frac{dv}{dx'} = -\frac{1+v}{2-4v}
